'''Isiolo Airport''' is an airport in [[Kenya]].

==Location==
Isiolo Airport {{airport codes|n/a|HKIS}} is located in, [[Isiolo District]], [[Eastern Province (Kenya)]], in the town of [[Isiolo]].

Its location is approximately {{convert|200|km|mi}}, by air, north of [[Nairobi International Airport]], the country<U+2019>s largest civilian airport.<ref>[http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Isiolo%20(Eastern)%20&toplace=Jomo%20Kenyatta%20Airport%20Nairobi%20(Nairobi%20Area)&fromlat=0.35&tolat=-1.3166667&fromlng=37.5833333&tolng=36.9333333  Flight Distance Between Nairobi And Isiolo With Map]</ref> The geographic coordinates of this airport are:0<U+00B0> 20' 37.00"N, 37<U+00B0> 35' 16.00"S (Latitude:0.343610; Longitude:37.587778).

==Overview==
Isiolo Airport is a small civilian airport, serving [[Isiolo]] and surrounding communities. Situated at {{convert|1067|m|ft}} above sea level,<ref>[http://www.aviador.es/Airports/Info/HKIS Elevation of Isiolo Airport]</ref> the [[airport]] has a single [[asphalt]] [[runway]] that measures {{convert|5000|ft|m}} long.<ref>[http://www.aircraft-charter-world.com/airports/africa/kenya.htm Length of Isiolo Airport Runway]</ref>

